16/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov will convoke a meeting of the National Security Council on Friday (16 July) to discuss issues related to Bulgarian participation in international peacekeeping missions. Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov and Army Chief General Nikola Kolev are expected to present reports. Parvanov's Bulgarian Socialist Party is insisting that the country refrain from participation in peacekeeping missions abroad.
In other news, a NATO AWACS plane arrived in Sofia on Thursday. It will provide air support during the Olympics in neighbouring Greece next month. NATO Airborne Early Warning and Control Forces Commander for Europe Major General Gary Winterberger is spending a couple days in Sofia as well. (Mediapool, BNT; bTV - 16/07/04)
